summary: Hartwick College is a private liberal arts college located in Oneonta, New York, founded in 1797 by John Christopher Hartwick as a Lutheran seminary. It evolved into a four-year college in 1928 and is known for its strong programs in nursing, business, and environmental science. The college features a unique January term (J Term) allowing students to focus on a single intensive course or experiential learning opportunity. Hartwick is also recognized for its Pine Lake Environmental Campus, a 145-acre outdoor education center supporting sustainability and field research.

name: Rush Limbaugh
summary: Rush Hudson Limbaugh III was born on January 12, 1951, and died on February 17, 2021. He was an American conservative radio talk show host, political commentator, and author, best known for The Rush Limbaugh Show, which aired nationally from 1988 to 2021. Limbaugh became a polarizing but influential figure in American politics, shaping conservative media and discourse for decades. His career spanned over 50 years, earning him accolades like the Presidential Medal of Freedom in 2020 while also sparking widespread controversy for his provocative rhetoric.
